Matt, just add another battery tray to the other side and add rack clusters
to a cutout on your overhead vent. If you pull your luggage tray that should
give you enough room for extra equipment and throwing away the radio and
installing your ILS/VOR along with the VHF/HF radio panels will compliment
your Collins rack. Now if you had an SC like mine, you could install it all
in the treasure chest with appropriate cooling system ! Also, you may want
to install ARINC 629 if you plan on installing a Connections Phased Array
antenna on your roof for future phone, internet, and cable TV options.

Food for thought!

